35
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:37,970
I heard Ms. Gil's parents
told you to marry Ms. Gil.

36
00:02:37,970 --> 00:02:39,637
You're not marrying her, are you?

37
00:02:39,637 --> 00:02:41,004
No, right?

38
00:02:41,004 --> 00:02:43,503
I don't care one way or another,
so mind your own business.

39
00:02:43,503 --> 00:02:44,804
You can't get married.

40
00:02:45,438 --> 00:02:48,970
I'm going to tell them
to stop pressuring you.

41
00:02:48,970 --> 00:02:51,503
They won't listen to you.

42
00:02:51,503 --> 00:02:57,037
Then I'm telling them you're
actually Kang Gyeong Jun.

43
00:02:57,737 --> 00:02:59,937
Jang Mary.

44
00:02:59,937 --> 00:03:01,404
Jang Mary.

45
00:03:04,937 --> 00:03:06,570
Why is she here?

46
00:03:08,204 --> 00:03:12,338
Why doesn't Mary want Da Ran
and Yun Jae to get married?

47
00:03:14,004 --> 00:03:15,670
- Jang Mary.
- Get out of the way.

48
00:03:17,071 --> 00:03:18,603
- Yun Jae.
- I have to run.

49
00:03:19,104 --> 00:03:19,837
Da Ran.

50
00:03:19,837 --> 00:03:21,904
Why are you here? Let's talk later.

51
00:03:22,603 --> 00:03:23,737
What the...

52
00:03:23,737 --> 00:03:25,037
What's going on?

53
00:03:25,970 --> 00:03:30,470
They must really be in love to have
gotten together behind our backs.

54
00:03:30,470 --> 00:03:33,237
They shouldn't have gone behind our backs.

55
00:03:33,237 --> 00:03:34,970
I told Da Ran I won't see either of them
if they're not getting married,

56
00:03:34,970 --> 00:03:36,570
so if they want to keep seeing each other,

57
00:03:36,570 --> 00:03:39,470
they should make their engagement official.

58
00:03:40,603 --> 00:03:42,870
Mr. Jang. Mrs. Jang.

59
00:03:43,404 --> 00:03:44,737
- Mary.
- Mary.

60
00:03:45,037 --> 00:03:46,804
There's something you need to know.

61
00:03:46,804 --> 00:03:48,371
Huh?

62
00:03:48,371 --> 00:03:50,304
Please don't be alarmed.

63
00:03:50,304 --> 00:03:51,704
Yun Jae.

64
00:03:52,503 --> 00:03:53,970
He's here.

65
00:03:53,970 --> 00:03:55,404
What do you want?

66
00:03:55,404 --> 00:03:59,637
I said I didn't want to see you
if you don't plan on marrying Da Ran.

67
00:04:00,004 --> 00:04:01,503
Hello.

68
00:04:01,503 --> 00:04:03,237
I'm telling them everything.

69
00:04:04,371 --> 00:04:06,237
Da Ran.

70
00:04:07,137 --> 00:04:08,438
Did she tell them?

71
00:04:08,438 --> 00:04:09,204
Not yet.

72
00:04:09,204 --> 00:04:10,970
Are you marrying him, Ms. Gil?

73
00:04:10,970 --> 00:04:12,470
Mary...

74
00:04:13,204 --> 00:04:15,237
You accepted the ring.

75
00:04:15,237 --> 00:04:16,670
Ring?

76
00:04:16,670 --> 00:04:19,137
He proposed to you, didn't he?

77
00:04:19,837 --> 00:04:21,904
Did you ask her to marry you?

78
00:04:22,770 --> 00:04:24,037
Yes.

79
00:04:24,037 --> 00:04:25,470
So what's your answer, Ms. Gil?

80
00:04:25,470 --> 00:04:26,837
Da Ran, what are you going to do?

81
00:04:26,837 --> 00:04:28,503
Are you marrying him?

82
00:04:30,470 --> 00:04:31,271
Um...

83
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:33,037
I told Da Ran how I felt about her.

84
00:04:33,037 --> 00:04:35,371
I'm now waiting for her decision.

85
00:04:35,371 --> 00:04:37,338
Nothing's set in stone yet,

86
00:04:37,338 --> 00:04:40,438
but Mary has jumped the gun.

87
00:04:40,438 --> 00:04:42,071
I'm sorry.

88
00:04:42,071 --> 00:04:44,204
Let's go, Jang Mary.

89
00:04:44,637 --> 00:04:47,537
I can always come back and tell them.

90
00:04:48,670 --> 00:04:51,304
We now know Yun Jae wants to marry you.

91
00:04:51,304 --> 00:04:52,770
What about you?

92
00:04:52,770 --> 00:04:57,503
Of course she'll marry him. She's
been seeing him behind our back.

93
00:04:58,970 --> 00:05:00,537
What's going on?

94
00:05:00,537 --> 00:05:03,271
Chung Sik, your sister's getting married.

95
00:05:03,271 --> 00:05:04,438
Yun Jae even gave her a ring.

96
00:05:04,438 --> 00:05:06,870
Is that why you rushed over here?

97
00:05:06,870 --> 00:05:11,071
Why did you go behind our back
if you were in such a rush to marry him?

98
00:05:12,970 --> 00:05:14,503
You saw, right?

99
00:05:14,503 --> 00:05:18,071
If Ms. Gil says yes, I'm going back
and spilling the beans.

100
00:05:18,071 --> 00:05:19,438
You're just a kid.

101
00:05:19,438 --> 00:05:21,570
I, on the other hand, look like an adult.
They'll believe me over you.

102
00:05:21,570 --> 00:05:23,637
An adult is no match for a bratty kid.

103
00:05:23,637 --> 00:05:24,637
You know that.

104
00:05:24,637 --> 00:05:27,904
Your mom and my dad didn't get married
because of my persistence.

105
00:05:27,904 --> 00:05:33,004
That's right. They couldn't get married,
because we were both brats.

106
00:05:33,004 --> 00:05:35,271
And what happened to my mom?

107
00:05:37,371 --> 00:05:40,503
If you tell them I'm Kang Gyeong Jun,

108
00:05:40,503 --> 00:05:42,338
I won't ever see you again.

109
00:05:49,904 --> 00:05:51,870
The furniture and appliances are there,

110
00:05:51,870 --> 00:05:54,004
and they did their wedding shoot.

111
00:05:54,004 --> 00:05:57,237
The wedding ceremony is all that's left.

112
00:05:57,237 --> 00:05:59,503
Don't let anyone know

113
00:05:59,503 --> 00:06:01,404
until the wedding date is confirmed.

114
00:06:02,470 --> 00:06:07,004
It's not peak season. It won't be
hard to find a wedding hall.

115
00:06:36,237 --> 00:06:38,804
If you want to know how
he really feels about you,

116
00:06:38,804 --> 00:06:41,104
let's just get married.

117
00:06:45,338 --> 00:06:50,704
I wonder if Yun Jae really
was planning to marry me.

118
00:07:06,870 --> 00:07:10,737
You did the right thing, Da Ran.

119
00:07:10,737 --> 00:07:12,704
You got the wedding ceremony out of the way

120
00:07:12,704 --> 00:07:15,470
and got us a beautiful house.

121
00:07:15,470 --> 00:07:17,737
The house is worth a lot more
than what you got it for, too.

122
00:07:18,537 --> 00:07:21,137
You're a perfect wife.

123
00:07:21,537 --> 00:07:23,237
Chung Sik.

124
00:07:26,970 --> 00:07:29,071
Take it. Take it.

125
00:07:40,404 --> 00:07:42,570
I wonder if that's how it'll be.

126
00:07:44,104 --> 00:07:47,071
But

127
00:07:47,071 --> 00:07:49,503
what if he didn't want to marry me?

128
00:07:51,004 --> 00:07:54,304
I'm so sorry, Da Ran.

129
00:07:54,304 --> 00:07:58,338
I had no idea you were this dense.

130
00:07:58,338 --> 00:08:01,837
The house went up in value.
Would you settle for that?

131
00:08:06,438 --> 00:08:10,404
[Divorce Petition]

132
00:08:10,404 --> 00:08:12,770
Will you just sign right here?

133
00:08:31,338 --> 00:08:33,304
You're still awake?

134
00:08:33,304 --> 00:08:35,071
Hi, mom.

135
00:08:41,870 --> 00:08:44,271
Are you still wavering?

136
00:08:44,937 --> 00:08:49,204
I'm not sure what Yun Jae's
true feelings are.

137
00:08:55,870 --> 00:08:57,904
And how do you feel about him?

138
00:08:59,404 --> 00:09:02,271
What's important is how you feel.

139
00:09:03,637 --> 00:09:07,537
Don't you love Yun Jae?

140
00:09:08,004 --> 00:09:11,503
I wish you won't worry too much
about Yun Jae's feelings

141
00:09:11,503 --> 00:09:14,204
like you did last time

142
00:09:14,204 --> 00:09:17,438
and just be faithful to your own feelings.

143
00:09:20,338 --> 00:09:22,737
You should go to bed.

144
00:09:39,104 --> 00:09:42,237
My feelings toward Yun Jae?

145
00:09:49,570 --> 00:09:52,570
I, Kang Gyeong Jun,

146
00:09:53,237 --> 00:09:55,870
vow to never

147
00:10:00,603 --> 00:10:02,970
fall in love with you.

148
00:10:19,171 --> 00:10:22,304
How much does

149
00:10:22,304 --> 00:10:25,037
Ms. Gil like Dr. Seo?

150
00:10:26,870 --> 00:10:28,804
My sister used to

151
00:10:28,804 --> 00:10:31,904
wait around the clock for him to call.

152
00:10:31,904 --> 00:10:35,503
She was pathetically in love.

153
00:10:36,870 --> 00:10:39,837
Then I won't have to worry about Ms. Gil.

154
00:10:47,204 --> 00:10:49,537
Jang Mary,

155
00:10:49,537 --> 00:10:54,304
how much do you like me?

156
00:10:55,104 --> 00:10:59,804
I know you like Kang Gyeong Jun,

157
00:10:59,804 --> 00:11:05,570
but we've gotten closer
through the pizza deal.

158
00:11:05,570 --> 00:11:10,271
Let's say your feelings for Gyeong Jun
are at 100. Where do I stand?

159
00:11:11,470 --> 00:11:13,937
30?

160
00:11:15,137 --> 00:11:16,904
30?

161
00:11:16,904 --> 00:11:18,904
I'd be happy with just 20.

162
00:11:18,904 --> 00:11:23,304
No. Just 10 will do.

163
00:11:25,503 --> 00:11:27,737
So?

164
00:11:29,071 --> 00:11:31,071
You're...

165
00:11:34,737 --> 00:11:36,271
Zero.

166
00:11:37,237 --> 00:11:39,271
Zero.

167
00:11:39,271 --> 00:11:40,837
Zero.

168
00:11:40,837 --> 00:11:42,271
Zero.

169
00:11:45,970 --> 00:11:47,204
Zero?

170
00:11:59,304 --> 00:12:00,770
Chung Sik,

171
00:12:00,770 --> 00:12:03,737
what did you get on your English test?

172
00:12:05,371 --> 00:12:07,637
Zero.

173
00:12:08,237 --> 00:12:09,537
Zero.

174
00:12:09,537 --> 00:12:12,603
What? 0%?

175
00:12:13,670 --> 00:12:17,770
That's not easy pull even by
guessing them all.

176
00:12:17,770 --> 00:12:20,637
Bring me your report card.

177
00:12:22,737 --> 00:12:25,271
You don't know how I feel.

178
00:12:27,438 --> 00:12:29,670
Where are you going? Gil Chung Sik!

179
00:12:29,670 --> 00:12:30,904
Did you hear?

180
00:12:30,904 --> 00:12:33,171
He opened a skin clinic in Gangnam.

181
00:12:33,171 --> 00:12:35,004
Yeah. It cost him $2 million, right?

182
00:12:35,004 --> 00:12:36,837
His wife's parents are rich.

183
00:12:36,837 --> 00:12:38,171
I didn't know that.

184
00:12:38,171 --> 00:12:39,404
How did you know?

185
00:12:39,404 --> 00:12:40,870
Didn't you see them at the wedding?

186
00:12:46,637 --> 00:12:48,104
Yun Jae,

187
00:12:48,970 --> 00:12:50,937
you'll be at the opening reception, right?

188
00:12:50,937 --> 00:12:53,137
It's all part of networking.

189
00:12:53,837 --> 00:12:57,338
I want to set up my own practice, too.
Will you co-sign a loan?

190
00:12:58,904 --> 00:13:01,737
I have something important to tend to.

191
00:13:01,737 --> 00:13:03,704
I have to run. See you.

192
00:13:04,970 --> 00:13:06,537
See you later.

193
00:13:29,804 --> 00:13:33,603
Doctor? Why are you back here?

194
00:13:34,371 --> 00:13:36,637
I was at the emergency room,

195
00:13:36,637 --> 00:13:40,304
but there were so many trauma victims
that I was traumatized.

196
00:13:40,304 --> 00:13:42,637
I need to rest, so go away.

197
00:13:42,637 --> 00:13:47,470
But doctors are supposed
to treat sick people.

198
00:13:47,470 --> 00:13:48,904
Do you want to co-sign a loan?

199
00:13:48,904 --> 00:13:50,137
Huh?

200
00:13:50,137 --> 00:13:52,704
That's the best way
to shoo away a pesky friend.

201
00:13:52,704 --> 00:13:54,904
Try it when you get older.

202
00:13:55,637 --> 00:13:57,670
Let me have a bite, Bunny Girl.

203
00:13:57,670 --> 00:13:59,137
My blood sugar level is low.

204
00:14:02,204 --> 00:14:05,737
You're an adult. Why are you
taking a kid's snack?

205
00:14:05,737 --> 00:14:09,104
I'm not an adult, so I can take her snack.

206
00:14:09,104 --> 00:14:11,271
Teddy Bear Boy,

207
00:14:11,271 --> 00:14:13,537
you sure talk a lot. You're a real pain.

208
00:14:13,537 --> 00:14:15,204
Do you want to co-sign a loan?

209
00:14:15,204 --> 00:14:16,237
Huh?

210
00:14:17,004 --> 00:14:18,704
Bunny Girl,

211
00:14:18,704 --> 00:14:20,637
you rock.

212
00:14:21,503 --> 00:14:25,371
- Good job.
- Isn't that something only adults say?

213
00:14:27,737 --> 00:14:31,770
Let's play a game.
Whoever has this doll has to be quiet.

214
00:14:45,904 --> 00:14:48,670
What is it that you want to ask me?

215
00:14:48,670 --> 00:14:53,104
How close were you and Yun Jae?

216
00:14:54,237 --> 00:14:57,204
It's something even Yun Jae doesn't remember,

217
00:14:57,204 --> 00:15:00,271
so why should I tell you?

218
00:15:00,271 --> 00:15:02,404
I need to know for sure
how Yun Jae feels about me.

219
00:15:02,404 --> 00:15:04,137
Please tell me.

220
00:15:04,503 --> 00:15:08,137
Yun Jae and I slept together.

221
00:15:08,904 --> 00:15:13,870
We were close enough to come
in and out of another's houses.

222
00:15:13,870 --> 00:15:16,570
You're lying, aren't you?

223
00:15:17,171 --> 00:15:19,804
Please be honest.

224
00:15:20,204 --> 00:15:22,438
What difference does it make if I'm lying?

225
00:15:22,438 --> 00:15:25,937
You don't think you're good enough for him,

226
00:15:25,937 --> 00:15:31,271
so you gave up before you got
to find out how he felt about you.

227
00:15:31,271 --> 00:15:34,371
Do you feel more confident
now that Yun Jae's back?

228
00:15:34,371 --> 00:15:36,037
Yes.

229
00:15:36,037 --> 00:15:38,204
I plan to be more self-assured

230
00:15:38,204 --> 00:15:41,304
and be true my feelings.

231
00:15:41,304 --> 00:15:42,937
Do what you will,

232
00:15:42,937 --> 00:15:46,737
but I don't care to encourage you.

233
00:15:46,737 --> 00:15:50,470
I'm merely trying to gain
some self-confidence.

234
00:15:50,470 --> 00:15:52,071
Can't you help me out here?

235
00:15:52,071 --> 00:15:53,104
No.

236
00:15:53,104 --> 00:15:55,304
You're really rotten, aren't you?

237
00:15:55,304 --> 00:15:57,104
At least I'm not pathetic like you.

238
00:15:57,104 --> 00:15:59,970
So did you have an affair
with Yun Jae or not?

239
00:15:59,970 --> 00:16:02,470
You have no right to be so brazen, you know?

240
00:16:02,470 --> 00:16:04,637
What I did may have been wrong,

241
00:16:04,637 --> 00:16:07,237
but I don't want things to go well for you.

242
00:16:07,770 --> 00:16:11,970
That's why I will never tell you.

243
00:16:26,503 --> 00:16:27,970
Hi.

244
00:16:56,804 --> 00:16:58,338
What's up?

245
00:17:00,770 --> 00:17:02,503
Hey.

246
00:17:02,503 --> 00:17:06,237
It's so hot that my face is flushed.

247
00:17:07,104 --> 00:17:08,804
Should I cool you down?

248
00:17:10,637 --> 00:17:12,371
How about some rain?

249
00:17:15,704 --> 00:17:18,404
Wow. It's like real rain.

250
00:17:26,204 --> 00:17:27,804
That was a short rain shower.

251
00:17:27,804 --> 00:17:29,104
My turn.

252
00:17:37,704 --> 00:17:39,770
- You're done for.
- Don't you dare.

253
00:17:43,503 --> 00:17:46,737
This one's monsoon rain. It will never stop.

254
00:17:47,304 --> 00:17:49,137
And this one's a typhoon.

255
00:17:50,804 --> 00:17:53,004
Hey. You're doing it on purpose, aren't you?

256
00:17:53,304 --> 00:17:54,737
Stop it.

257
00:17:58,603 --> 00:18:03,637
Gil Teacher, I don't think
I'm the only typhoon victim.

258
00:18:06,870 --> 00:18:08,104
My purse!

259
00:18:08,104 --> 00:18:10,237
There are important documents in it.

260
00:18:38,271 --> 00:18:40,637
I have to turn this in tomorrow.

261
00:18:40,637 --> 00:18:43,004
You were acting like the goddess of rain

262
00:18:43,004 --> 00:18:44,670
or something.

263
00:18:45,338 --> 00:18:47,438
And who started it?

264
00:18:47,438 --> 00:18:50,503
Who asked you to goof off
with a kid anyway?

265
00:18:54,804 --> 00:18:56,704
