My ring's gone.

268
00:19:02,271 --> 00:19:04,404
You lost it?

269
00:19:06,770 --> 00:19:08,037
You're such a scatterbrain.

270
00:19:08,037 --> 00:19:11,371
You've waited for that ring for ages.
How can you lose it in less than a day?

271
00:19:13,404 --> 00:19:15,304
It's not here.

272
00:19:16,237 --> 00:19:18,271
Maybe I lost it somewhere else.

273
00:19:18,271 --> 00:19:21,171
Look more carefully.

274
00:19:25,537 --> 00:19:26,904
Never mind.

275
00:19:26,904 --> 00:19:29,037
If it's lost, so be it.

276
00:19:29,037 --> 00:19:30,438
What?

277
00:19:35,637 --> 00:19:38,770
Maybe you're relieved that it's lost.

278
00:19:39,637 --> 00:19:43,870
I thought I had gotten over him,
but then that ring showed up.

279
00:19:43,870 --> 00:19:47,404
I don't think I can figure out
how he really felt about me.

280
00:19:47,404 --> 00:19:50,104
Now that I've lost the ring,
I just won't think about it anymore.

281
00:19:50,104 --> 00:19:51,737
Gil Da Ran,

282
00:19:51,737 --> 00:19:55,271
all your thinking and pondering
has confused you even more again.

283
00:19:56,037 --> 00:19:58,104
How can you give up so easily?

284
00:19:58,104 --> 00:19:59,704
I have to give up

285
00:19:59,704 --> 00:20:02,770
if I'm to discuss marriage
with a kid like you.

286
00:20:02,770 --> 00:20:04,438
No else knows but I know who you really are.

287
00:20:04,438 --> 00:20:05,837
Don't make excuses.

288
00:20:05,837 --> 00:20:08,037
That's not what's going on.
You're still not confident.

289
00:20:08,037 --> 00:20:10,503
You're scared of waiting and
finding out how he really feels.

290
00:20:11,737 --> 00:20:14,837
How can I just go through with this
when I don't know how he feels?

291
00:20:14,837 --> 00:20:17,171
Only young kids like you
can be that reckless.

292
00:20:17,171 --> 00:20:20,404
Even a young kid like me only gave up
after I was turned out.

293
00:20:20,404 --> 00:20:23,338
You, however, only agonized over it
and then gave up without even trying.

294
00:20:23,338 --> 00:20:26,037
That doesn't make you an adult.
That makes you a loser.

295
00:20:26,037 --> 00:20:28,204
Fine. I'm a loser.

296
00:20:28,204 --> 00:20:30,837
Don't expect much of an
immature loser like me then.

297
00:20:32,704 --> 00:20:34,837
Fine. I won't.

298
00:20:34,837 --> 00:20:38,970
I'm just going to marry anyone
Yun Jae's mother tells me to.

299
00:20:38,970 --> 00:20:41,670
That means you'll never get
a chance to find out.

300
00:20:56,704 --> 00:20:58,104
[Supplementary Class Schedule:
2013 Summer Session]

301
00:21:13,438 --> 00:21:16,004
Has your sister decided to get married?

302
00:21:16,004 --> 00:21:18,503
She says she hasn't made up her mind yet.

303
00:21:18,503 --> 00:21:20,171
Really?

304
00:21:20,737 --> 00:21:23,670
Then all I have to do is
make up with Gyeong Jun.

305
00:21:23,670 --> 00:21:25,204
Jang Mary,

306
00:21:27,570 --> 00:21:32,704
although I may be a zero to you right now,

307
00:21:32,704 --> 00:21:35,837
I'll spread a white sheet of paper

308
00:21:35,837 --> 00:21:38,704
in my heart and wait for you

309
00:21:38,704 --> 00:21:40,503
to give me even just a single point.

310
00:21:42,137 --> 00:21:43,137
Chung Sik. Chung Sik.

311
00:21:43,137 --> 00:21:45,204
Take this out to the recycling bin.

312
00:21:45,204 --> 00:21:46,603
Mom,

313
00:21:46,603 --> 00:21:48,237
can't you see I'm busy right now?

314
00:21:48,237 --> 00:21:49,438
You do it.

315
00:21:49,438 --> 00:21:54,670
Fine. I'm throwing out the magazines
and DVDs I found under your bed.

316
00:22:03,137 --> 00:22:04,870
White sheet of paper?

317
00:22:07,503 --> 00:22:08,904
Mary.

318
00:22:08,904 --> 00:22:11,737
They're not mine. They're my dad's.

319
00:22:11,737 --> 00:22:13,204
Mary.

320
00:22:14,503 --> 00:22:15,570
Mom!

321
00:22:15,570 --> 00:22:17,137
Why did you bring these out?

322
00:22:17,137 --> 00:22:20,404
That's why I told you to take them
to the recycling bin.

323
00:22:20,404 --> 00:22:22,503
Mary was here. This is so embarrassing.

324
00:22:22,503 --> 00:22:25,804
You drive me crazy, mom.

325
00:22:25,804 --> 00:22:28,237
It's okay. I understand.

326
00:22:28,237 --> 00:22:29,870
I hate you.

327
00:22:32,371 --> 00:22:35,804
Why's he so riled up over nothing?

328
00:22:35,804 --> 00:22:37,570
I hate you, too.

329
00:22:37,570 --> 00:22:39,204
All I wanted him to do
was take out the trash.

330
00:23:20,037 --> 00:23:23,037
It's fine when it's in books or on screen...

331
00:23:29,737 --> 00:23:32,904
[Supplementary Class Schedule:
2013 Summer Session]

332
00:23:36,037 --> 00:23:38,438
I hope the vice principal chews her out.

333
00:23:54,804 --> 00:23:56,570
Hyo Sang's on his way.

334
00:23:56,570 --> 00:23:59,037
His piggy bank's gone.

335
00:23:59,037 --> 00:24:01,704
He must have run away like he did
when he was in middle school.

336
00:24:01,704 --> 00:24:03,970
Good grief.

337
00:24:04,770 --> 00:24:08,204
Chung Sik will take Mary's call,

338
00:24:08,204 --> 00:24:11,603
and Mary will do what
Gyeong Jun tells her to.

339
00:24:20,470 --> 00:24:22,371
Gym?

340
00:24:29,171 --> 00:24:30,770
Why's he here?

341
00:24:30,770 --> 00:24:34,937
Do you how much was in the piggy bank?

342
00:24:34,937 --> 00:24:37,104
Around $100.

343
00:24:37,104 --> 00:24:39,204
He couldn't have gotten that far then.

344
00:24:39,204 --> 00:24:42,904
It's important to find him before
he leaves the near vicinity.

345
00:24:42,904 --> 00:24:45,271
I've contacted Chung Sik's friends,

346
00:24:45,271 --> 00:24:46,837
so we'll be able to locate him.

347
00:24:46,837 --> 00:24:47,904
Thank you.

348
00:24:47,904 --> 00:24:49,670
Da Ran, get him something to drink.

349
00:24:51,338 --> 00:24:52,804
Please don't worry.

350
00:24:53,503 --> 00:24:56,737
We're sorry we asked you come
all this way in this terrible heat.

351
00:24:57,371 --> 00:24:59,071
Thank you.

352
00:25:01,737 --> 00:25:03,870
She can see the gym teacher for all I care.

353
00:25:05,404 --> 00:25:06,804
Yun Jae.

354
00:25:07,537 --> 00:25:09,237
Yun Jae.

355
00:25:09,870 --> 00:25:13,970
You must have come over because
you were worried about Chung Sik.

356
00:25:15,204 --> 00:25:16,271
Uh... Yes.

357
00:25:16,271 --> 00:25:19,770
Come in. Let's talk inside.

358
00:25:20,404 --> 00:25:23,037
Da Ran, Yun Jae's here.

359
00:25:24,371 --> 00:25:25,937
Come in.

360
00:25:25,937 --> 00:25:28,603
You didn't have to call Yun Jae.

361
00:25:29,371 --> 00:25:32,371
Hyo Sang's here, so don't worry.

362
00:25:32,371 --> 00:25:36,037
But he came all this way,
because he was worried.

363
00:25:36,037 --> 00:25:38,770
Da Ran, why don't you two

364
00:25:38,770 --> 00:25:41,937
look for Chung Sik at nearby internet cafes,

365
00:25:41,937 --> 00:25:43,937
comic book stores, and karaokes?

366
00:25:43,937 --> 00:25:45,438
We'll do that.

367
00:25:45,438 --> 00:25:47,204
That will be useless.

368
00:25:47,204 --> 00:25:48,804
If Chung Sik's really intent
on running away,

369
00:25:48,804 --> 00:25:51,870
he wouldn't be anywhere
you'd expect him to be at.

370
00:25:51,870 --> 00:25:53,503
I'll look for him,

371
00:25:53,503 --> 00:25:55,204
so don't worry and go to bed.

372
00:25:55,204 --> 00:25:57,171
Hyo Sang's right.

373
00:25:57,171 --> 00:26:00,870
Da Ran, why don't you go and
look for Chung Sik with Hyo Sang?

374
00:26:00,870 --> 00:26:03,271
There's no need to bother Yun Jae.

375
00:26:03,271 --> 00:26:05,603
I want to help out.

376
00:26:05,603 --> 00:26:07,037
Who knows?

377
00:26:07,037 --> 00:26:11,438
I might find Chung Sik more quickly
than the runaway expert here.

378
00:26:12,637 --> 00:26:15,937
Fine. Go for it then.

379
00:26:23,204 --> 00:26:27,104
The gym teacher's a runaway expert,
but I'm the runaway's classmate.

380
00:26:27,837 --> 00:26:29,404
But they don't know that, do they?

381
00:26:36,637 --> 00:26:37,837
Gyeong Jun.

382
00:26:37,837 --> 00:26:39,438
Gil Chung Sik ran away from home.

383
00:26:41,037 --> 00:26:42,204
We have to find him,

384
00:26:42,204 --> 00:26:45,404
so get his best friends and come over.

385
00:26:45,404 --> 00:26:47,404
And don't take the gym teacher's calls.

386
00:26:47,404 --> 00:26:48,704
Okay.

387
00:26:53,470 --> 00:26:55,104
You're still here?

388
00:26:55,104 --> 00:26:57,304
I'm strategizing.

389
00:26:57,304 --> 00:26:58,670
Excuse me then.

390
00:27:01,404 --> 00:27:03,338
Did you get in touch with Mary?

391
00:27:03,338 --> 00:27:06,503
Why should I tell you?
You're not on my team.

392
00:27:07,338 --> 00:27:08,704
Mr. Na.

393
00:27:10,737 --> 00:27:12,837
That pitcher's still hasn't left the mound.

394
00:27:12,837 --> 00:27:17,171
Mr. Na, I'll look for Chung Sik
with that team.

395
00:27:17,171 --> 00:27:18,637
Sure.

396
00:27:24,537 --> 00:27:26,137
Is Mary coming?

397
00:27:26,137 --> 00:27:27,737
Yup.

398
00:27:33,338 --> 00:27:34,937
Mary.

399
00:27:34,937 --> 00:27:36,304
Has Gil Chung Sik called?

400
00:27:36,304 --> 00:27:38,004
His phone's turned off.

401
00:27:39,071 --> 00:27:40,204
Where do you think he might be?

402
00:27:40,204 --> 00:27:44,804
Our other friend Geun Chan ran away once.
He slept in the underpass by Seoul Station.

403
00:27:44,804 --> 00:27:47,503
- Underpass?
- Chung Sik wouldn't do that.

404
00:27:47,503 --> 00:27:50,004
I bet he's at a sauna.

405
00:27:50,004 --> 00:27:55,837
He once spend the night at a sauna
where Jun Seok's sister works.

406
00:27:55,837 --> 00:27:57,371
A sauna?

407
00:28:00,404 --> 00:28:02,071
I'm an expert.

408
00:28:03,104 --> 00:28:05,670
I must read the mind of the runaway teen.

409
00:28:07,438 --> 00:28:10,237
He ran away on impulse,

410
00:28:10,237 --> 00:28:12,503
so he couldn't have gotten far.

411
00:28:13,603 --> 00:28:15,937
A dark place near the house...

412
00:28:16,804 --> 00:28:19,037
I'll start with the park.

413
00:28:20,137 --> 00:28:22,937
Gil Chung Sik, here I come.

414
00:28:22,937 --> 00:28:24,904
Mr. Na's coming to find you.

415
00:28:39,503 --> 00:28:41,470
Traces of a runaway.

416
00:28:42,804 --> 00:28:44,137
[Help Wanted]

417
00:28:44,137 --> 00:28:46,970
He was looking for a job.

418
00:28:46,970 --> 00:28:50,404
Once he gets a job, it'll be
even harder to find him.

419
00:28:52,704 --> 00:28:54,770
I have to find him tonight.

420
00:29:02,171 --> 00:29:03,870
He has eaten.

421
00:29:07,704 --> 00:29:10,704
It's been less than an hour since he left.

422
00:29:13,137 --> 00:29:17,470
Why did he leave though?

423
00:29:22,104 --> 00:29:23,737
Mosquitoes.

424
00:29:25,804 --> 00:29:28,704
If he wanted to get away from mosquitoes,

425
00:29:28,704 --> 00:29:31,204
he would have gone indoors.

426
00:29:31,737 --> 00:29:33,637
If he's nervous, he wouldn't have returned

427
00:29:33,637 --> 00:29:36,104
to a place he's already been to.

428
00:29:38,704 --> 00:29:40,004
Where can he be?

429
00:29:43,438 --> 00:29:46,537
A place his friends know
but his parents don't...

430
00:29:46,537 --> 00:29:49,670
I need info from Chung Sik's best friends.

431
00:29:49,670 --> 00:29:52,271
Why aren't they picking up?

432
00:29:52,271 --> 00:29:53,737
The person you're trying to reach...

433
00:29:56,537 --> 00:29:58,603
Are we just going to sit here?

434
00:30:01,404 --> 00:30:02,937
We'll hear from Mary soon.

435
00:30:02,937 --> 00:30:04,438
Chung Sik has run away from home.

436
00:30:04,438 --> 00:30:06,603
Why are you so laid back?

437
00:30:06,603 --> 00:30:09,037
What would you know? You've always been

438
00:30:09,037 --> 00:30:10,770
a model student.

439
00:30:10,770 --> 00:30:13,503
I defied my mom, too. It got very serious.

440
00:30:13,503 --> 00:30:14,670
Over what?

441
00:30:14,670 --> 00:30:16,603
Did you say you were going to Harvard
instead of Seoul National?

442
00:30:16,603 --> 00:30:18,338
I need another drink.

443
00:30:18,338 --> 00:30:20,204
Answer the phone if Mary calls.

444
00:30:23,037 --> 00:30:25,704
He must have really gone
against his mother's wishes.

445
00:30:29,704 --> 00:30:31,304
Hi, Mary.

446
00:30:32,904 --> 00:30:34,603
Are you with Gyeong Jun?

447
00:30:34,603 --> 00:30:36,970
Yeah. Did you get a hold of Chung Sik?

448
00:30:36,970 --> 00:30:38,271
No.

449
00:30:39,404 --> 00:30:41,804
Are you and Gyeong Jun
looking for Chung Sik together?

450
00:30:42,537 --> 00:30:46,104
Hasn't Chung Sik's friends heard from him?

451
00:30:48,970 --> 00:30:51,704
One of them thinks he might be
at the underpass by Seoul Station.

452
00:30:52,171 --> 00:30:53,037
Seoul Station?

453
00:30:53,037 --> 00:30:55,171
You go and look for him there,

454
00:30:55,171 --> 00:30:58,870
and tell Gyeong Jun to meet me
at the sauna in Noryangjin.

455
00:30:58,870 --> 00:31:01,204
Okay.

456
00:31:06,704 --> 00:31:11,137
Mary's meeting you at the sauna in
Noryangjin. I'm going to Seoul Station.

457
00:31:11,137 --> 00:31:12,338
Go.

458
00:31:12,338 --> 00:31:13,204
Are you sure you can go alone?

459
00:31:13,204 --> 00:31:15,438
Look for him at the dry sauna
with Mary. Hurry.

460
00:31:46,104 --> 00:31:47,071
Dr. Seo.

461
00:31:47,071 --> 00:31:49,237
Defiance must be kept short.

462
00:31:49,237 --> 00:31:51,338
Otherwise, you'll miss your window
of opportunity to cut it short.

463
00:31:51,338 --> 00:31:53,037
But I don't plan to keep it short.

464
00:31:53,037 --> 00:31:54,737
I'm not going home.

465
00:31:54,737 --> 00:31:57,503
I'm not seeing my mom again.

466
00:31:57,503 --> 00:31:59,503
You may say that, but I bet

467
00:31:59,503 --> 00:32:02,371
there's no way you believe
you really won't ever see her again.

468
00:32:02,371 --> 00:32:04,104
I don't care if I don't get to see her again.

469
00:32:04,104 --> 00:32:05,904
You know Kang Gyeong Jun, right?

470
00:32:06,338 --> 00:32:07,637
Yes.

471
00:32:07,637 --> 00:32:10,404
His mother died while he was being defiant.

472
00:32:10,404 --> 00:32:15,104
He thought he wouldn't care if he never
got to see her again, but she died.

473
00:32:15,104 --> 00:32:19,404
Defy your mom more often if you have to,
but don't drag this out.

474
00:32:19,404 --> 00:32:22,037
Keep an eye on how your mom's doing.

475
00:32:23,338 --> 00:32:26,904
Is my mom okay?

476
00:32:26,904 --> 00:32:29,570
You can go home and check for yourself.

477
00:32:29,570 --> 00:32:33,770
If you can't bear to go back just like this,
tell your mom what you want.

478
00:32:33,770 --> 00:32:36,637
I'll do my best to negotiate on your behalf.

479
00:32:37,770 --> 00:32:41,338
Could you get her to let me
study in the States?

480
00:32:41,338 --> 00:32:44,004
I'll see if I can negotiate
a trip to the U.S. for you.

481
00:32:44,004 --> 00:32:45,637
Gil Chung Sik.

482
00:32:46,037 --> 00:32:47,637
Gyeong...

483
00:32:47,637 --> 00:32:49,171
Dr. Seo.

484
00:32:52,271 --> 00:32:54,470
Jang Mary,

485
00:32:54,470 --> 00:32:57,071
did you come to look for me?

486
00:32:57,071 --> 00:32:58,737
Are we spending the night here?

487
00:32:58,737 --> 00:33:00,237
It'll be fun.

488
00:33:01,104 --> 00:33:02,737
Time to go home.

489
00:33:02,737 --> 00:33:04,204
Okay.

490
00:33:04,904 --> 00:33:07,438
Gil Da Ran's at a sauna
near Seoul Station, right?

491
00:33:07,438 --> 00:33:08,470
No.

492
00:33:08,470 --> 00:33:10,304
She's at an underpass
where the homeless are.

493
00:33:10,304 --> 00:33:11,670
- What?
- What?

494
00:33:11,670 --> 00:33:13,037
Gil Chung Sik.

495
00:33:16,770 --> 00:33:18,404
Chung Sik.

496
00:33:20,037 --> 00:33:21,770
Chung Sik.

497
00:33:25,970 --> 00:33:27,670
Chung Sik.

498
00:33:32,637 --> 00:33:34,137
Spare some change.

499
00:33:45,637 --> 00:33:47,704
You startled me.

500
00:33:47,704 --> 00:33:50,338
Are you out of your mind?
How could you come here alone?

501
00:33:51,071 --> 00:33:54,570
I'm fine. Why are you all worked up?

502
00:33:55,338 --> 00:33:56,770
Da Ran.

503
00:34:02,704 --> 00:34:04,271
Gil Chung Sik.

504
00:34:04,271 --> 00:34:05,704
You're a jerk.

505
00:34:05,704 --> 00:34:07,570
You'll be the death of me.

506
00:34:07,570 --> 00:34:09,037
What did I do?

507
00:34:09,371 --> 00:34:11,071
You'd better get your act together.

508
00:34:12,770 --> 00:34:14,037
Don't hit me.

509
00:34:14,037 --> 00:34:15,237
You...

510
00:34:20,438 --> 00:34:21,904
I'm sorry.

511
00:34:21,904 --> 00:34:23,537
Chung Sik,

512
00:34:23,537 --> 00:34:24,937
where have you been?

513
00:34:24,937 --> 00:34:28,470
Get a good night's sleep.
We'll talk tomorrow morning.

514
00:34:28,470 --> 00:34:30,570
Good grief.

515
00:34:33,371 --> 00:34:34,137
Mom.

516
00:34:34,137 --> 00:34:37,137
Yes, my baby.

517
00:34:37,137 --> 00:34:39,670
- I'm glad you're back.
- Yun Jae found him?

518
00:34:40,970 --> 00:34:42,037
Yes.

519
00:34:42,037 --> 00:34:46,004
Tell Yun Jae I'd like to see him later too

520
00:34:46,004 --> 00:34:48,204
for lunch or dinner.

521
00:34:53,071 --> 00:34:57,304
Your dad seems to have come around,
because he brought Chung Sik back.

522
00:35:08,970 --> 00:35:12,404
Why are you crying, Mary?

523
00:35:13,071 --> 00:35:17,271
Gyeong Jun's

524
00:35:17,271 --> 00:35:21,071
mad at me because

525
00:35:21,870 --> 00:35:25,503
I lied again

526
00:35:26,371 --> 00:35:30,438
and put you in harm's way.

527
00:35:30,438 --> 00:35:33,637
He's very angry.

528
00:35:34,470 --> 00:35:38,470
I...

529
00:35:38,470 --> 00:35:41,438
I didn't do it on purpose.

530
00:35:42,804 --> 00:35:45,237
It's okay.

531
