594
00:41:12,870 --> 00:41:14,338
Is it because of this?

595
00:41:15,603 --> 00:41:18,304
Enjoy the food.

596
00:41:18,304 --> 00:41:20,470
- These are all yours.
- Thank you.

597
00:41:23,271 --> 00:41:24,804
This is better.

598
00:41:27,637 --> 00:41:28,937
Let me see.

599
00:41:28,937 --> 00:41:31,438
Your former students are here.

600
00:41:32,171 --> 00:41:33,837
Undo the top button.

601
00:41:49,371 --> 00:41:51,104
Hello, Mr. Gil.

602
00:41:51,104 --> 00:41:52,870
Hi.

603
00:41:58,004 --> 00:41:59,837
I brought these for you.

604
00:42:01,904 --> 00:42:03,737
Thanks.

605
00:42:11,438 --> 00:42:13,637
- Min Gyu...
- Here you go.

606
00:42:13,637 --> 00:42:15,404
Thanks.

607
00:42:28,137 --> 00:42:30,237
You're the student who always

608
00:42:30,237 --> 00:42:34,770
watched those two with a rock in your hand.

609
00:42:34,770 --> 00:42:36,637
And you're the teacher
who always watched them

610
00:42:36,637 --> 00:42:40,204
from behind a tree with
a handkerchief in your hand.

611
00:42:42,937 --> 00:42:48,704
As you age, you realize
beauty really is nothing.

612
00:42:49,338 --> 00:42:54,804
Maybe it's this shabby restaurant,
but he certainly looks old.

613
00:42:54,804 --> 00:42:56,503
Very old.

614
00:43:00,371 --> 00:43:02,404
I didn't plan to go back home,

615
00:43:02,404 --> 00:43:05,603
but Mary came to look for me
and was so insistent

616
00:43:05,603 --> 00:43:06,904
that I caved in.

617
00:43:09,937 --> 00:43:12,037
Your father must have
given you a good beating.

618
00:43:12,037 --> 00:43:13,171
No, he didn't.

619
00:43:13,171 --> 00:43:14,404
It was his mom.

620
00:43:14,404 --> 00:43:17,704
I let her beat me so she'd feel better.

621
00:43:17,704 --> 00:43:19,271
Be good to your moms.

622
00:43:21,271 --> 00:43:23,104
Keep your defiance short.

623
00:43:23,104 --> 00:43:26,371
Otherwise, you'll miss your "windex"
of opportunity to cut it short.

624
00:43:26,804 --> 00:43:28,271
You mean "window of opportunity," right?

625
00:43:30,104 --> 00:43:32,271
Just forget about studying in the States.

626
00:43:32,271 --> 00:43:33,670
No.

627
00:43:33,670 --> 00:43:36,404
I must go wherever Mary goes.

628
00:43:38,404 --> 00:43:43,503
But Mary's probably with Kang Gyeong Jun...

629
00:44:00,104 --> 00:44:01,837
What are you doing here?

630
00:44:02,503 --> 00:44:06,804
I got you your favorite.

631
00:44:11,804 --> 00:44:13,704
It's all melted.

632
00:44:19,338 --> 00:44:21,171
It's all my fault.

633
00:44:22,037 --> 00:44:24,137
I ruined everything.

634
00:44:28,837 --> 00:44:30,338
It's not your fault.

635
00:44:31,104 --> 00:44:33,104
It's hot out.

636
00:44:34,637 --> 00:44:38,804
And what happened to my mom
wasn't your fault either.

637
00:44:39,171 --> 00:44:43,603
I won't be a brat anymore.

638
00:44:45,204 --> 00:44:48,603
I won't just do whatever I feel like.

639
00:45:15,338 --> 00:45:16,371
Don't over think it.

640
00:45:17,704 --> 00:45:20,438
We're simply taking things back
to the way they should have been.

641
00:45:32,804 --> 00:45:35,404
I will no longer waver over what I think

642
00:45:35,404 --> 00:45:37,704
Yun Jae's feelings toward me may have been.

643
00:45:39,037 --> 00:45:42,104
I was thinking of telling you
to help you out,

644
00:45:42,104 --> 00:45:43,404
but should I not?

645
00:45:43,404 --> 00:45:45,004
Do what you will.

646
00:45:45,004 --> 00:45:48,603
What you say won't affect me anyway.

647
00:45:48,603 --> 00:45:50,870
I have to be a reliable adult.

648
00:45:50,870 --> 00:45:55,570
and to that end, I need to be
strong and self-assured.

649
00:45:56,438 --> 00:45:58,470
Really?

650
00:45:58,470 --> 00:46:02,637
You might need a little help

651
00:46:02,637 --> 00:46:05,104
to test how strong and self-assured you are.

652
00:46:06,104 --> 00:46:07,670
Let me help you on that front.

653
00:46:08,171 --> 00:46:10,338
Fine.

654
00:46:11,670 --> 00:46:15,470
Like the pine atop Namsan Peak
in our national anthem,

655
00:46:15,470 --> 00:46:20,071
I will stand firm as if wrapped in armour.

656
00:46:27,037 --> 00:46:29,537
Where is it?

657
00:46:31,004 --> 00:46:32,804
Now that I've even likened
myself to a pine tree,

658
00:46:32,804 --> 00:46:36,371
I have to find that ring.

659
00:46:37,704 --> 00:46:39,037
It's hot out. What's up?

660
00:46:39,037 --> 00:46:43,104
I need to find the ring. Where can it be?

661
00:46:44,470 --> 00:46:47,237
You should've looked for it right away.
You're such a slowpoke.

662
00:46:48,004 --> 00:46:50,870
It's too hot out. Add to it
by being annoying.

663
00:46:50,870 --> 00:46:52,670
You're hot?

664
00:46:55,137 --> 00:46:57,937
That's nice. Keep that coming.

665
00:46:59,404 --> 00:47:01,603
Stronger.

666
00:47:05,570 --> 00:47:07,503
My arm hurts.

667
00:47:16,570 --> 00:47:20,271
You had found it.

668
00:47:22,637 --> 00:47:24,904
Why are you just staring at it? Take it.

669
00:47:31,837 --> 00:47:34,237
I think I still love him.

670
00:47:35,304 --> 00:47:40,537
I'm sure my heart still yearns for him.

671
00:47:41,404 --> 00:47:46,537
I know the person you're seeing
right now is not Kang Gyeong Jun.

672
00:47:47,770 --> 00:47:49,870
I won't be a baby anymore

673
00:47:49,870 --> 00:47:53,603
and keep you from loving the man you want.

674
00:47:53,603 --> 00:47:57,937
I'll help you grow up into a fine young man.

675
00:48:04,570 --> 00:48:06,970
Kang Gyeong Jun,

676
00:48:06,970 --> 00:48:08,970
marry me.

677
00:48:10,603 --> 00:48:12,737
I'll raise you well.

678
00:48:21,603 --> 00:48:24,770
If I'm still like this
by the time I reach 20,

679
00:48:24,770 --> 00:48:26,704
let's just go our separate ways.

680
00:48:29,071 --> 00:48:33,837
I will stand firm as if wrapped in armour.

681
00:48:33,837 --> 00:48:35,537
Go, go!

682
00:48:38,737 --> 00:48:40,304
What's wrong?

683
00:48:40,304 --> 00:48:42,137
Do you think this is a bad idea?

684
00:48:42,670 --> 00:48:45,570
I know Seo Yun Jae's not here
to do it himself,

685
00:48:45,570 --> 00:48:47,404
but it's really sad to put on
your own engagement ring.

686
00:48:49,271 --> 00:48:50,904
I'll do it in his stead.

687
00:49:01,537 --> 00:49:03,037
Let's make this work.

688
00:49:06,438 --> 00:49:08,804
I shall repeat my vow.

689
00:49:08,804 --> 00:49:12,104
I will never

690
00:49:12,104 --> 00:49:14,037
be nice to you.

691
00:49:14,037 --> 00:49:17,037
Why not? You said I could
think of you as Yun Jae.

692
00:49:17,037 --> 00:49:20,104
What if you get confused

693
00:49:20,104 --> 00:49:21,637
and try to jump me?

694
00:49:21,637 --> 00:49:23,071
No, I won't.

695
00:49:23,937 --> 00:49:27,371
I will continue being a jerk
for my own safety.

696
00:49:27,371 --> 00:49:28,704
Fine.

697
00:49:28,704 --> 00:49:32,570
Since I'm the adult, I'll let you be a baby.

698
00:49:33,171 --> 00:49:35,970
Let's inform our parents and
get this over and done with.

699
00:49:36,404 --> 00:49:37,904
Let's go.

700
00:49:38,304 --> 00:49:40,004
Go, go.

701
00:49:40,737 --> 00:49:42,004
Go, go.

702
00:49:43,537 --> 00:49:45,503
No refunds.

703
00:49:46,237 --> 00:49:49,404
How will you manage the
consequences of black magic?

704
00:49:51,804 --> 00:49:53,104
Then write me another spell.

705
00:49:53,104 --> 00:49:55,837
Readjusting a spell

706
00:49:55,837 --> 00:49:57,704
costs an additional $30.

707
00:49:57,704 --> 00:50:02,570
This time, make sure they don't fall
in love even if they're together 24/7.

708
00:50:02,570 --> 00:50:04,637
Okay.

709
00:50:05,970 --> 00:50:11,171
Go behind the door and
divert the evil spirits.

710
00:50:18,770 --> 00:50:20,404
Not him.

711
00:50:20,404 --> 00:50:22,237
He's not pure.

712
00:50:22,770 --> 00:50:24,870
It's a misunderstanding, Mary.

713
00:50:24,870 --> 00:50:27,470
The porn...

714
00:50:27,470 --> 00:50:31,104
Was my dad's.

715
00:50:31,104 --> 00:50:35,204
I'm as pure as a white sheet of paper.

716
00:50:38,937 --> 00:50:41,204
He does seem pure.

717
00:50:41,204 --> 00:50:43,204
Go and distract the evil spirits.

718
00:50:43,204 --> 00:50:44,970
You can read right through me.

719
00:50:46,704 --> 00:50:48,637
Mary,

720
00:50:48,637 --> 00:50:51,470
I'm distracting the evil spirits for you.

721
00:50:57,537 --> 00:51:03,537
What you want is to keep two people from

722
00:51:03,537 --> 00:51:04,970
falling in love, right?

723
00:51:04,970 --> 00:51:07,137
Even if they get married,

724
00:51:07,137 --> 00:51:11,338
make sure they won't ever
fall for each other.

725
00:51:12,137 --> 00:51:16,438
This one has to work.

726
00:51:18,037 --> 00:51:23,304
I'd still like to see you even
after Yun Jae gets married.

727
00:51:23,970 --> 00:51:28,637
And please introduce me to Dr. Seo
when he comes to Korea.

728
00:51:28,637 --> 00:51:34,404
I've wanted to meet him not because
he's Yun Jae's dad but a great doctor.

729
00:51:35,204 --> 00:51:38,204
Yun Jae's father says he can't
come to Korea right away,

730
00:51:38,204 --> 00:51:42,204
but they're still pushing
ahead with the wedding.

731
00:51:44,537 --> 00:51:45,737
Oh?

732
00:51:45,737 --> 00:51:48,870
Yun Jae has this book too.

733
00:51:48,870 --> 00:51:50,670
Is it a famous storybook?

734
00:51:50,670 --> 00:51:53,004
It's never been released.

735
00:51:53,438 --> 00:51:57,837
Yun Jae's father put it together
to remember someone by.

736
00:51:58,537 --> 00:52:00,237
Dr. Seo wrote this?

737
00:52:00,237 --> 00:52:01,770
Yes.

738
00:52:01,770 --> 00:52:06,004
Yun Jae's father painted this
when Yun Jae was young.

739
00:52:06,004 --> 00:52:07,503
Oh...

740
00:52:07,503 --> 00:52:09,503
What is it about?

741
00:52:10,937 --> 00:52:15,037
The story is that if one
child helps another child,

742
00:52:15,037 --> 00:52:19,204
the latter will save yet another child.

743
00:52:31,804 --> 00:52:35,904
It's a good thing we didn't throw these out.

744
00:52:37,737 --> 00:52:40,204
It's beautiful.

745
00:52:56,204 --> 00:52:57,970
Mary,

746
00:52:57,970 --> 00:53:02,338
are you really planning to go
to my sister's wedding like that?

747
00:53:02,338 --> 00:53:05,071
Yes. I have to.

748
00:53:07,338 --> 00:53:10,470
But...

749
00:53:10,470 --> 00:53:13,338
Isn't that poor etiquette?

750
00:53:13,338 --> 00:53:17,570
You'll outshine the bride.

751
00:53:17,570 --> 00:53:19,470
Precisely.

752
00:53:19,470 --> 00:53:23,637
I'll never leave her side.

753
00:53:23,637 --> 00:53:27,937
But then it'll look like
the groom has two brides.

754
00:53:27,937 --> 00:53:29,438
Precisely.

755
00:53:38,304 --> 00:53:40,970
Tomorrow's the day, Kang Gyeong Jun.

756
00:53:41,438 --> 00:53:44,004
You're becoming an adult.

757
00:53:44,004 --> 00:53:46,037
I'll open it for you.

758
00:53:46,737 --> 00:53:47,637
But I can do it.

759
00:53:47,637 --> 00:53:49,037
No.

760
00:53:49,637 --> 00:53:53,970
This delineates our relationship.

761
00:53:53,970 --> 00:53:57,304
This is something I can drink
but you can't.

762
00:53:57,304 --> 00:53:59,603
Let's not forget that.

763
00:53:59,603 --> 00:54:04,071
Let's always keep this boundary in mind.

764
00:54:04,071 --> 00:54:05,438
Fine.

765
00:54:05,438 --> 00:54:07,570
If I'm not back in my body

766
00:54:07,570 --> 00:54:09,804
by the time I can legally open this myself,

767
00:54:09,804 --> 00:54:11,304
we'll share a drink

768
00:54:11,304 --> 00:54:13,737
and then say our goodbyes.

769
00:54:55,537 --> 00:54:57,637
Gil Da Ran,

770
00:54:57,637 --> 00:55:02,037
are you happy to be going to China alone?

771
00:55:02,037 --> 00:55:03,404
Wait until you start working.

772
00:55:03,404 --> 00:55:06,304
It's not easy to get time off.

773
00:55:06,304 --> 00:55:07,737
And what about you?

774
00:55:07,737 --> 00:55:10,204
I'll figure something out.

775
00:55:10,204 --> 00:55:13,204
You didn't go on the class trip last year,
did you? Gyeongju is great.

776
00:55:13,204 --> 00:55:15,371
Drop me off and then head over to Gyeongju.

777
00:55:15,371 --> 00:55:18,404
Our parents think we're off together
on our honeymoon,

778
00:55:18,404 --> 00:55:19,970
so don't get caught.

779
00:55:19,970 --> 00:55:21,404
Don't worry about me.

780
00:55:21,404 --> 00:55:24,071
Just make sure you don't run into
anyone you know in China.

781
00:55:24,704 --> 00:55:26,804
I can't wait to see the Forbidden City.

782
00:55:26,804 --> 00:55:29,237
And I've been dying to try Peking Duck.

783
00:55:29,237 --> 00:55:31,704
Ni hao ma. Xie xie.

784
00:55:45,004 --> 00:55:46,071
Thanks.

785
00:55:46,071 --> 00:55:49,071
I'll show you pictures of
the Great Wall when I get back.

786
00:55:49,071 --> 00:55:50,637
Off I go!

787
00:55:54,438 --> 00:55:57,404
She doesn't even ask me
if I want to come with her.

788
00:56:08,503 --> 00:56:09,770
Gil Da Ran.

789
00:56:10,937 --> 00:56:13,970
Gil Da Ran! Gil Da Ran!

790
00:56:22,904 --> 00:56:24,470
Wow, Gil Da Ran.

791
00:56:24,470 --> 00:56:26,970
I guess you won't get a chance
to say "ni hao ma."

792
00:56:33,204 --> 00:56:34,737
My passport.

793
00:56:50,804 --> 00:56:52,770
What's up?

794
00:56:52,770 --> 00:56:57,271
I think I left my passport in the car
along with the guidebook.

795
00:56:57,271 --> 00:56:58,637
Can you check?

796
00:56:58,637 --> 00:57:00,237
Your passport?

