Your passport?

799
00:57:11,870 --> 00:57:14,438
Let's see.

800
00:57:14,438 --> 00:57:16,304
Look at that. It's here.

801
00:57:16,304 --> 00:57:17,204
It's there?

802
00:57:17,204 --> 00:57:19,804
Then bring it over to the airport right away.

803
00:57:19,804 --> 00:57:22,438
But I've already come quite far.

804
00:57:22,438 --> 00:57:26,737
I'll step on the gas though
and try to get there ASAP.

805
00:57:26,737 --> 00:57:28,804
You have to hurry.

806
00:57:28,804 --> 00:57:30,204
Okay.

807
00:57:58,904 --> 00:58:00,670
Gil Teacher.

808
00:58:02,404 --> 00:58:05,237
Is it too late?

809
00:58:16,537 --> 00:58:18,171
[Forbidden City]

810
00:58:23,171 --> 00:58:25,537
You were working hard
on your Chinese phrases.

811
00:58:25,537 --> 00:58:29,371
What a shame you won't get to say "ni hao ma."

812
00:58:30,237 --> 00:58:32,704
I think the chef's Chinese.

813
00:58:32,704 --> 00:58:34,137
Do you want to talk to him?

814
00:58:34,870 --> 00:58:37,404
I wanted Peking Duck.

815
00:58:37,404 --> 00:58:40,271
Chinese noodles are just as good.

816
00:58:40,271 --> 00:58:42,037
Enjoy.

817
00:58:46,137 --> 00:58:49,470
Are you that disappointed?

818
00:58:51,404 --> 00:58:53,204
Oh, well.

819
00:58:53,937 --> 00:58:55,804
Let's go home.

820
00:58:56,537 --> 00:58:58,004
How about this?

821
00:58:58,004 --> 00:58:59,670
Let's go on a trip.

822
00:59:00,438 --> 00:59:03,071
Forget about your vacation
and my school trip.

823
00:59:03,071 --> 00:59:04,870
Let's go on our honeymoon.

824
00:59:09,537 --> 00:59:12,770
Yun Jae got married.

825
00:59:14,004 --> 00:59:18,171
As always, you're so aloof toward Yun Jae.

826
00:59:18,171 --> 00:59:19,937
That's not true.

827
00:59:21,770 --> 00:59:24,338
There was something I had to look into.

828
00:59:24,338 --> 00:59:27,404
What's more important than your son?

829
00:59:27,404 --> 00:59:29,904
That child.

830
00:59:29,904 --> 00:59:32,438
I heard his mother died.

831
00:59:33,304 --> 00:59:34,338
Pardon?

832
00:59:34,338 --> 00:59:36,338
She got shot in the States.

833
00:59:37,271 --> 00:59:39,804
She was gunned down by armed robbers.

834
00:59:41,904 --> 00:59:44,037
Then what about the child?

835
00:59:44,037 --> 00:59:49,304
I'm looking for him right now.

836
00:59:49,304 --> 00:59:52,338
I'm sure Yun Jae will understand.

837
00:59:59,104 --> 01:00:00,503
Where should we go?

838
01:00:01,171 --> 01:00:03,970
You only have 5 days off, so we can't go far.

839
01:00:03,970 --> 01:00:06,770
We could go to a resort in Guam or Saipan.

840
01:00:06,770 --> 01:00:10,104
If you really want to see the Forbidden City,
we can go to China, too.

841
01:00:10,104 --> 01:00:13,704
I really want to go to China.

842
01:00:13,704 --> 01:00:14,804
Why?

843
01:00:14,804 --> 01:00:17,670
I want to see the Great Wall.

844
01:00:17,670 --> 01:00:18,737
Alright.

845
01:00:19,338 --> 01:00:23,870
Off to the Great Wall we go.

846
01:00:27,438 --> 01:00:31,870
Why did you have your luggage
and passport in your car though?

847
01:00:31,870 --> 01:00:35,004
I always keep these in my car.

848
01:00:36,137 --> 01:00:39,271
I'm a jetsetter. It's my lifestyle.

849
01:00:39,271 --> 01:00:43,171
So that means you could've come
to China with me if I had asked earlier.

850
01:00:43,171 --> 01:00:45,570
It didn't sit well with me
to leave you behind.

851
01:00:45,570 --> 01:00:47,438
Really?

852
01:00:47,438 --> 01:00:51,737
You should've said so. I could've
come with you if you wanted me to.

853
01:00:51,737 --> 01:00:55,304
But it's a bit weird asking you to come
with me on my honeymoon.

854
01:00:55,304 --> 01:00:57,171
Why?

855
01:00:58,470 --> 01:01:00,137
A honeymoon is...

856
01:01:00,137 --> 01:01:01,338
Gil Teacher,

857
01:01:01,338 --> 01:01:03,171
don't get carried away.

858
01:01:03,171 --> 01:01:04,537
I would never ask you

859
01:01:04,537 --> 01:01:08,037
to do what other couples do on honeymoons.

860
01:01:08,037 --> 01:01:09,770
Of course not.

861
01:01:12,338 --> 01:01:14,404
I need to withdraw some cash.

862
01:01:26,304 --> 01:01:28,804
Why am I so giddy?

863
01:01:29,237 --> 01:01:31,870
It'll be embarrassing
if Gyeong Jun catches on.

864
01:01:36,904 --> 01:01:38,704
Shanghai.

865
01:01:38,704 --> 01:01:40,570
Beijing.

866
01:01:44,804 --> 01:01:47,804
Let's see. Do I need to exchange money?

867
01:02:25,837 --> 01:02:27,570
Gyeong Jun.

868
01:02:29,770 --> 01:02:31,837
What's wrong?

869
01:02:37,137 --> 01:02:40,537
I think

870
01:02:40,537 --> 01:02:43,004
I just revisited my own body.

871
01:02:47,870 --> 01:02:50,204
Congratulations, Gil Teacher.

872
01:02:52,503 --> 01:02:55,171
I think Seo Yun Jae is about to return.

873
01:03:30,770 --> 01:03:32,804
What should I sing at my sister's wedding?

874
01:03:32,804 --> 01:03:35,338
- "Wedding Proposal."
- That's so cliche.

875
01:03:35,338 --> 01:03:36,670
"I Will Never Let You Go."

876
01:03:39,171 --> 01:03:42,438
I don't think it's a good wedding song.

877
01:03:42,438 --> 01:03:43,837
Sing it!

878
01:03:44,737 --> 01:03:46,371
I will never let you go even if it kills me.

879
01:03:46,371 --> 01:03:48,071
How can I let you go?

880
01:03:48,071 --> 01:03:51,904
If you're going to leave,
mend my broken heart.

881
01:03:51,904 --> 01:03:53,137
Sing.

882
01:03:53,804 --> 01:03:55,904
 I will never let you go even if it kills me 

883
01:03:55,904 --> 01:03:57,137
You.

884
01:03:57,137 --> 01:04:00,637
 How can I let you go? 

885
01:04:00,637 --> 01:04:01,970
Chung Sik.

886
01:04:01,970 --> 01:04:10,137
 If you're going to leave,
mend my broken heart 

887
01:04:10,137 --> 01:04:13,204
 So that it doesn't hurt 
